    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-12-16T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-12-16T23:00:00-05:00" n="228"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d228">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">816.01/22: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in El Salvador</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Curtis</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">San Salvador</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-12-16T22:00:00-06:00"
                            >December 16, 1931—10 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 17—12:08 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>121. Your 69, December 16, 7 p.m. Mexican Minister informs me that in accordance
                    with the Estrada doctrine<note n="27" xml:id="d228fn27">Institute Americano de
                        Derecho y Legislacion Comparada, <hi rend="italic">La Doctrina Estrada</hi>
                        (Mexico, Publicaciones del Institute Americano de Derecho y Legislacion
                        Comparada, 1930), and <hi rend="italic">La Opinion Universal sobre La
                            Doctrina Estrada</hi>, etc. (Mexico, Publicaciones del Institute
                        Americano de Derecho y Legislacion Comparada, 1931).</note> relations
                    between Mexico and El Salvador have not been interrupted but that he has taken
                    no action beyond acknowledging receipt of a note informing him of the change of
                    government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Curtis</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
